# Next.js 15 App Router Patterns

## App Router Structure
- Use the new App Router (`src/app/` directory)
- Place pages in `src/app/` with appropriate route segments
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts
- Use `page.tsx` for route components

## File Conventions
- `page.tsx` - Route components (required)
- `layout.tsx` - Shared layouts
- `loading.tsx` - Loading UI
- `error.tsx` - Error boundaries
- `not-found.tsx` - 404 pages

## Metadata and SEO
- Use `metadata` export in layout files
- Set proper title, description, and Open Graph tags
- Use dynamic metadata for dynamic routes
- Implement structured data when appropriate

## Data Fetching
- Use Server Components by default
- Use `use client` directive only when needed
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use Next.js caching strategies

## Performance
- Enable Turbopack for development (`--turbopack`)
- Use Image component for optimized images
- Implement proper loading states
- Use Suspense boundaries for code splitting
